# Cursor Rules for Useful Tools React

You are an expert React/TypeScript developer working on **Useful Tools React** — a dark-themed pregnancy tracking and productivity web app. Always follow these rules precisely when generating or modifying code.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | React 18.3 + TypeScript 5.5 (strict mode) |
| Build | Vite 5.4 — env files in `environments/` directory |
| Styling | TailwindCSS 3.4 (dark-first, glass morphism, mobile-first) |
| Animation | Framer Motion 11 |
| State | Zustand 5 with `persist` middleware |
| Routing | React Router DOM v6 |
| Backend | Firebase 11 (Auth + **Realtime Database** + Storage) |
| Auth | Firebase Auth + Azure AD via `@azure/msal-react` |
| Data fetching | `@tanstack/react-query` v5 |
| Real-time | Socket.io client v4 (live share) |
| i18n | react-i18next — EN + VI locales |
| Forms | react-hook-form v7 |
| Icons | lucide-react |
| Toast | `toast` from `@/components/ui/Toast` (not sonner directly) |
| Dates | date-fns v4 |
| Charts | chart.js + react-chartjs-2 |
| Class util | `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` (clsx + tailwind-merge) |

---

## Design System

- **Background**: `bg-slate-950` with gradient orbs (`primary-500/20`, `accent-500/15`)
- **Glass cards**: `bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/10 rounded-xl`
- **Primary**: purple — `primary-500` (#d946ef), `primary-600` (#c026d3)
- **Accent**: orange — `accent-500` (#f97316)
- **Baby palette**: `baby-pink`, `baby-blue`, `baby-mint`, `baby-lavender`, `baby-peach`
- **Dark mode**: class-based; set via `document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', ...)`
- **Fonts**: `font-sans` (DM Sans), `font-display` (Playfair Display), `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono)

---

## File & Project Conventions

- **Naming**: kebab-case for all files — `baby-tracker.tsx`, `use-countdown.ts`
- **File size**: Max ~200 lines; split larger files into focused modules
- **Imports**: Always use `@/` alias — never relative `../../`
- **Types**: All shared types/interfaces in `src/types/index.ts`; use enums for domain constants
- **Services**: All Firebase/API calls in `src/services/`; never in components or stores
- **Primary DB**: Firebase Realtime Database via `src/services/realtimeDb.ts` helpers
- **Firestore**: Used only for file upload metadata in `storageService.ts`
- **UI Primitives**: Always use existing components from `src/components/ui/` — never raw HTML elements:
  - `Button` — all clickable actions
  - `Input` — text, number, password inputs (supports `label`, `error`)
  - `DatePicker` — date selection (`label`, `value`, `onChange`, `minDate`, `maxDate`, `centered` for modals)
  - `Card`, `Modal`, `Badge`, `Progress`, `Spinner`, `Toast`

### Project Structure

```
src/
+-- components/layout/   # Sidebar, Header, Layout
+-- components/ui/       # Button, Card, Modal, Input, Badge, Progress, etc.
+-- config/              # firebase.ts, authConfig.ts, constants.ts
+-- hooks/               # Custom React hooks
+-- i18n/locales/        # en.json, vi.json
+-- lib/utils.ts         # cn(), calculateBMI, etc.
+-- pages/               # Route-level components
+-- services/            # Firebase / API service layer
+-- stores/              # Zustand stores
+-- types/index.ts       # All shared types
```

---

## Code Patterns

### Page Component

```typescript
// src/pages/new-feature.tsx
import { motion } from "framer-motion";
import { useTranslation } from "react-i18next";
import { Card } from "@/components/ui";
import { useAuthStore } from "@/stores/authStore";

export const NewFeaturePage: React.FC = () => {
  const { t } = useTranslation();
  const { user } = useAuthStore();

  return (
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      className="container mx-auto p-4"
    >
      <h1 className="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        {t("newFeature.title")}
      </h1>
      <Card>{/* content */}</Card>
    </motion.div>
  );
};
```

### Zustand Store

```typescript
// src/stores/example-store.ts
import { create } from "zustand";
import { persist, createJSONStorage } from "zustand/middleware";
import type { Item } from "@/types";

interface ExampleState {
  items: Item[];
  isLoading: boolean;
  setItems: (items: Item[]) => void;
  setLoading: (loading: boolean) => void;
}

export const useExampleStore = create<ExampleState>()(
  persist(
    (set) => ({
      items: [],
      isLoading: false,
      setItems: (items) => set({ items }),
      setLoading: (isLoading) => set({ isLoading }),
    }),
    { name: "example-storage", storage: createJSONStorage(() => localStorage) }
  )
);
```

### Realtime DB Service

```typescript
// src/services/example-service.ts
import type { Item } from "@/types";
import { createItem, deleteItem, listenCollection, updateItem } from "./realtimeDb";

const PATH = "items";

export const listenItems = (onChange: (items: Item[]) => void) =>
  listenCollection<Item>(PATH, onChange);

export const createItemEntry = async (item: Item) => {
  const { id, ...payload } = item;
  return createItem(PATH, payload);
};

export const updateItemEntry = (id: string, item: Partial<Item>) =>
  updateItem(PATH, id, item);

export const deleteItemEntry = (id: string) => deleteItem(PATH, id);
```

### Custom Hook with Firebase Listener

```typescript
// src/hooks/use-items.ts
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import type { Item } from "@/types";
import { listenItems } from "@/services/example-service";

export const useItems = () => {
  const [items, setItems] = useState<Item[]>([]);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    const unsubscribe = listenItems((data) => {
      setItems(data);
      setIsLoading(false);
    });
    return () => unsubscribe(); // Always clean up listeners
  }, []);

  return { items, isLoading };
};
```

### Form with react-hook-form

```typescript
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { useTranslation } from "react-i18next";
import { toast } from "@/components/ui/Toast";
import { Input, Button } from "@/components/ui";

interface FormData { name: string; }

export const ExampleForm: React.FC<{ onSuccess: () => void }> = ({ onSuccess }) => {
  const { t } = useTranslation();
  const { register, handleSubmit, reset, formState: { errors, isSubmitting } } =
    useForm<FormData>();

  const onSubmit = async (data: FormData) => {
    try {
      await myService.save(data);
      toast.success(t("form.saved"));
      reset();
      onSuccess();
    } catch {
      toast.error(t("form.error"));
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className="space-y-4">
      <Input
        {...register("name", { required: t("form.required") })}
        error={errors.name?.message}
      />
      <Button type="submit" isLoading={isSubmitting}>{t("common.save")}</Button>
    </form>
  );
};
```

---

## i18n Rules

- Every user-facing string uses `t("key.subkey")` — no hardcoded text
- Add to **both** `src/i18n/locales/en.json` and `vi.json` together
- Keys describe context: `babyTracker.addKickButton`, not `btn1`

---

## Security Rules

- Env vars in `environments/` — never commit `.env.local`
- Validate/sanitize all user inputs before Firebase writes
- Check `isAuthenticated` from `useAuthStore()` before protected content
- Prevent XSS in any user-generated HTML

---

## Anti-patterns ❌

- Don't use `any` in TypeScript
- Don't hardcode user-facing text — always `t()`
- Don't commit credentials or env files
- Don't create "enhanced" duplicate files — edit originals
- Don't use inline styles — TailwindCSS only
- Don't skip try/catch in async operations
- Don't bypass auth checks
- Don't write files over 200 lines without splitting
- Don't ignore TS or ESLint errors
- Don't write raw Firebase calls outside `src/services/`
- Don't use relative imports — always `@/`
- Don't use class components
- Don't use raw HTML `<input>`, `<button>`, `<select>` — use `Input`, `Button`, `DatePicker` from `@/components/ui`

---

